mods.abstract: The California Magazine of Western Square and Round Dancing by the Square Dancers of Southern California. This edition includes a table of contents which lists the following: "From the Floor", "Square Dance Date Book", "On the Record and Record Report", "As I See It, by Bob Osgood", "How are They Dancing, by Bill Blinn", "Americana: Black-Eyed Suzie, by Terry Golden", "The Dancer's Walkthru", "Vox Saltator: The Square Dancer Speaks Up", "Programming: Add a Dash of Color, by Bob Page", "Can It Be True? Square Dancing Banned in Vietnam by Ted and Lanny McQuaide", "Schoolhouse Square Dance, by Betty Auckland", "Ladies on the Square: Ideas for Club Cookery", "Style Series: Variations for All Four-Part 1", "New Basics-Reject or Retain, by Carter Humphrey", "'Round the Outside Ring", "Workshop", "The Caller of the Month: John Strong", "Paging the Roundancers: Gerry and Peggy Mace", and "Experimental Lab: Dixie Style to an Ocean Wave".
